pages.text: $(l:materials/Yttrium)Yttrium$(/l) $(l:materials/Barium)barium$(/l) $(l:materials/Copper)copper$(/l) oxide (YBCO) is a family of crystalline chemical compounds, famous for displaying high-temperature superconductivity. It includes the first material ever discovered to become superconducting above the boiling point of liquid nitrogen (77 K) at about 90 K.
